  "text": "The Kubernetes sig-node kubelet component ownership map includes four major components:\n\n1. **Pod Lifecycle Manager**: Located in `pkg/kubelet/pod_workers.go`, this component manages the lifecycle of pods on the node. The main implementation is the `podWorkers` struct (line 551) which implements the `PodWorkers` interface (line 142). This manager handles pod synchronization, updates, and termination.\n\n2. **Container Runtime Interface (CRI) Client**: The CRI client is implemented in `staging/src/k8s.io/cri-client/pkg/remote_runtime.go`. The main type is `remoteRuntimeService` struct (line 47), which implements the gRPC-based container runtime interface for communicating with container runtimes like containerd, CRI-O, etc.\n\n3. **Volume Manager**: Located in `pkg/kubelet/volumemanager/volume_manager.go`, this component manages the attachment and mounting of storage volumes to pods. The main implementation is the `volumeManager` struct (line 243) which implements the `VolumeManager` interface (line 93).\n\n4. **Device Plugin Manager**: Located in `pkg/kubelet/cm/devicemanager/manager.go`, this component manages device plugins and allocates hardware devices (GPUs, accelerators, etc.) to pods. The main implementation is the `ManagerImpl` struct (line 62).\n\nAdditionally, a generic plugin manager exists in `pkg/kubelet/pluginmanager/plugin_manager.go` which provides the framework for plugin management used by device plugins and other plugin types."
